description:
The Need for Speed

Technology Documentary hosted by William Hootkins, published by Discovery Channel broadcasted as part of DC Extreme Machines series in 2000 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

From the British speed heroes of the 1930s to the first man to break the sound barrier; man is constantly obsessed with pushing the boundaries of speed, often at the ultimate cost - their own lives. This is a celebration of our adrenaline-fuelled passion to go faster than ever before. So sit back, buckle up and prepare to be overwhelmed by the need for speed.




9)  Adrenaline Junkies 
Adrenaline Junkies are obsessives who are hooked on danger in all shapes and forms. They rely on the performance from their speed machines to fulfill their dreams. These people can be found on land, in the sea and up in the sky. The Californian desert racers custom build their cars to go faster and faster over some of the most dangerous roads imaginable. Patrick de Gayardon and Barbara Brighetti practice extreme parachuting and sky surfing often reaching speeds of over 120 mph; and meet Shaun Baker, an extreme kayaker who takes his canoe over waterfalls. These adrenaline junkies are always just one step away from disaster, always pushing both man and machine to the limits of their endurance.

Narrator: William Hootkins
Director: Stephen Marsh
Producer: Alice Harper
Executive Producer: Stuart Carter
Executive Producer for the Learning Channel : Susan Winslow
Produced By Pioneer Productions For The Learning Channel
Pioneer Productions TLC
2000 Discovery Communications, Inc.




